questions.text:
What is the running time of the following pseudo code in Big-Oh notation:

```cpp
int XXX(int n)
{
    if(n < 6)
        cout << "too small";
    else
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
        {
            cout << "just right";
        }
    return n;
}

void main()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
        a = XXX(i);
}
```

questions.explanation:
Insertion sort proceeds by sorting the first \( i+1 \) elements in the \( i \)-th iteration:
- Initial: {13, 10, 4, 19, 2, 30, 11, 6}
- Iteration 1 (key 10): {10, 13, 4, 19, 2, 30, 11, 6}
- Iteration 2 (key 4): {4, 10, 13, 19, 2, 30, 11, 6}
- Iteration 3 (key 19): {4, 10, 13, 19, 2, 30, 11, 6}
- Iteration 4 (key 2): {2, 4, 10, 13, 19, 30, 11, 6}
- Iteration 5 (key 30): {2, 4, 10, 13, 19, 30, 11, 6}
The resulting array is {2, 4, 10, 13, 19, 30, 11, 6}.

